% backtrace_operands.trx
% Demonstrates the operand-stack snapshot in the backtrace.
%
% Pushes seven values of different types before triggering an error.
% The snapshot shows the top 8 operands with their type names and
% compact values, ordered top-of-stack first.

/boom { 1 0 div } def
true
42
3.14
(hello)
/aname
[ 1 2 3 ]
boom
